The unique mechanism of action as well as its additional properties, such as biological and chemical stability, low toxicity and the possibility of other chemical designs, makes the metalocarbanes interesting compounds for further research aimed at the development of effective anti-HIV drugs, says Pavlina Rezacova, Head of the Laboratory for Structural Biology of the Institutes of Organic Chemistry and Biochemistry and the Institute of Molecular Genetics of the Academy of Sciences.
