Sale of accident cars on the Internet
In the past October, the Solera Autoonline Group purchased a platform on the Internet for the sale of motorbikes and motorcycles.
This purchase meant the payment of EUR 59.5 million for 85% of the company's capital, which could increase to the remaining 15% next year.
The purpose of this purchase was to offer its customers more services and added value, with the possibility of accessing a huge international market.
This review and purchase service is exclusively addressed to industry professionals, such as insurance companies, consultants, car rental companies, workshops, scrap shops and car dealers, who must be registered prior to their activities.
This platform was founded in Germany in 1996 and manages more than 650,000 operations throughout Europe, 500,000 of which alone in Germany.
Their main markets are Spain, Greece, Poland and Turkey.
The website today has more than 1,500 registered sellers and 4,000 auditors.
Every day 3,000 ads are managed and 100 new ads are added every day to the Spanish market.
