Cost estimate of the workshop in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, the company Audatex ensures that the user is given a cost estimate in just four steps:identification of the vehicle, search of the spare part, creation and creation of a cost estimate.
The ease of handling of these systems is a fundamental condition, especially in order to convince the older professionals, who are usually more or less opposed to the use of these new computer technologies.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, 666 of which are passenger cars, 109 off-road cars, 137 motorcycles, 78 small hauliers and 44 trucks.
Of course you need a computer with Internet connection to use.
After the model to be repaired has been identified on the basis of the chassis number, a chart of the respective model appears and after that the replacement part required is selected.
The user can include variables such as the price for the hours of work, surcharges or discounts and thereafter can have the cost estimate printed and passed on to his customers.
However, AudaTaller is not a tool for assessing such as AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalogue.
The main difference between the two systems is that the workshop-oriented working time does not include estimated working hours.
The cost of using this tool is 350 Euro per year, an amount that the customer can pay without further notice.
Currently, the company Audatex is working on offering these images in three-dimensional format.
